description: The Chartbooks for 2001 and 2002 contain 37 tables, charts, and graphs that present highlights from the Statistical Compendiums, including comparisons of use and reimbursement for major eligibility groups (aged, disabled, adults, children, dual eligibles) and types of drugs, and state rankings on key measures. The 2003 through 2008 Chartbooks contain 54 tables, charts, and graphs, since a number of additional graphs have been added to show trends from 1999 to 2008.
title: Medicaid Pharmacy Benefit Use and Reimbursement
